{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01AZiwtTuWBdF8xELB87kVP5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is healthy with 3 nodes (green). I also validated resilience by restarting the node that depends on the additional CA.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Current state: healthy 3-node Elasticsearch cluster, status `green`.**\n\n### What I found\nThe cluster (`es-cluster`, ES 7.17.9) runs as a 3-replica StatefulSet with transport TLS (`xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true`, verification mode `certificate`). The key design point of this scenario:\n\n- A `cert-selector` init container gives **es-cluster-0/1** transport node certs signed by **CA1**, while **es-cluster-2** gets a cert signed by **CA2** (the \"additional\" CA).\n- For all nodes to form one cluster, every node's transport trust store (`es-transport-ca-bundle` configMap, mounted at `config/transport-ca/ca.crt`) must trust **both** CAs. If CA2 were missing, es-cluster-2's transport handshake would be rejected and it couldn't join → a degraded 2-node cluster.\n\n### What I verified / did\n1. `_cluster/health` → `green`, `number_of_nodes: 3`, all shards active, no unassigned shards.\n2. The `es-transport-ca-bundle` configMap contains **both** `es-ca-1` and `es-ca-2` certificates, and confirmed all three running pods have the 2-cert bundle mounted on disk.\n3. **Validated durability** by deleting `es-cluster-2` (the CA2-dependent node). It came back with a fresh CA2-signed cert (new IP `10.244.0.106`) and rejoined cleanly — cluster stayed `green` at 3 nodes, proving the peers correctly trust the additional CA.\n\nNo operators or CRDs were used. The trust bundle was already complete and the cluster is at a healthy, resilient 3-node `green` state."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":604,"cache_read_input_tokens":48327,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":604},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9c0b1bd-6b5c-4ada-aaac-d492f503165f","uuid":"e1e93d51-b2c7-467b-91f5-32b2788e5ec9","request_id":"req_011CcAtZP7qyX2CnWxM9BQ89"}
